stylometry:
The data mining method we used was cluster analysis.

The first thiing we did was take raw data and standardize it.
We then used the euclidean distance formula to find the distance between the standardized values of our different data and the cluster centers
The objective function consisted of the sum of the squared distances of each of the cluster centers

Solver was set to change the cluster centers to minimize the objective funtion which resulted in cluster categories that contained data that was closest to the cluster centers.
